1.title: Episode #9.1

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

1.plot: Shaun analyzes the Liberal Party's controversial election of Scott Morrison as the new prime minister, the growing number of female Liberal MPs accusing their party of bullying them, accusations of corruption against Home Affairs Minister Peter Dutton, former PM Tony Abbott's idea that Australia should rely on nuclear energy, and the new PM's announcement of royal commission into Aged Care.

2.title: Episode #9.2

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

2.plot: Did Rupert Murdoch plot to replace the prime minister? Are the politicians taking the incident with tampered strawberries too seriously? Is extremism on the rise in the Liberal Party? A revisionist take on Sir Henry Parkes is shown.

3.title: Episode #9.3

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

3.plot: The government's attempt to take control over ABC makes Shaun and his colleagues very nervous. The wreck of Captain Cook's ship has been discovered. Financial companies agree to give back some of what they had stolen.

4.title: Episode #9.4

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

4.plot: Shaun talks pork barrelling, presents a Putin-inspired calendar featuring the prime minister, asks a movie nerd about rumors that ABC will be merged with another entity, and gives an update on the nuclear submarines bought from France.

5.title: Episode #9.5

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

5.plot: The British royals are coming for a visit. Religious beliefs of an anti-gay baker raise larger questions about discrimination. The government rejects appeals to let Doctors Without Borders visit Nauru. Is xenophobia on the rise?

6.title: Episode #9.6

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

6.plot: The Liberal Party loses the by elections. Who's to blame? Will Australia stop global warming? Will the embassy be moved to Jerusalem? Will the royal commission into aged care quality and safety begin? Are grassroots candidates any good?

7.title: Episode #9.7

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

7.plot: Shaun remembers the bad good old days. What are former prime ministers up to? Can the government go against the energy companies? Trump comments on Jamal Khashoggi's murder. The British royal visit leads to horrendous news puns.

8.title: Episode #9.8

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

8.plot: The National Party kicks out a far right member. Nauru refugees are allowed into Australia. Pro-government journalist Alan Jones attacks the critics. Is Victoria really plagued by crime? What's happening with people's health records?

9.title: Episode #9.9

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

9.plot: The prime minister goes on a bus tour around the country by plane. The One Nation Party gets a new ally. A new fake show about a sinister home designer who plans to ruin the family that hired him is previewed.

1.title: Episode #6.1

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

1.plot: To raise money for charity the San Antonio Spurs basketball team is miniaturised, injected into Iggy Pop's head and given just 60 minutes to find five living brain cells which it can challenge to a game of 'hoops'.

2.title: Episode #6.2

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

2.plot: Thriller in which a man wakes to discover that his left kidney has been removed and replaced with a nuclear bomb set to go off at 1800 hours, exactly when he's supposed to be at his son's school concert.

3.title: Episode #6.3

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

3.plot: During a sudden moon storm, a space baker is abandoned by his fellow astronauts. Talking to himself so we understand what he's thinking, the space baker must ration a single sachet of yeast to survive.

4.title: Episode #6.4

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

4.plot: Haunted by the death of her refrigerator expansion valve, a young woman moves to Tuscany to begin a new life - only to discover that you can't escape your past (the broken expansion valve follows her there).

5.title: Episode #6.5

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

5.plot: A dying man decides to embark on a 2000km road trip with his son to visit something or other one last time. But as a surprise, the son buys a pair of plane tickets, so they end up flying instead.

6.title: Episode #6.6

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

6.plot: On a secret mission to kidnap a Nazi ocelot rumoured to know the codes to a submarine, a team of British commandos parachute into Berlin Zoo behind enemy lions.

7.title: Episode #6.7

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

7.plot: A time-travelling scientist accidentally steps on a butterfly in dinosaur times. When he returns to 2016, he discovers to his horror that his tiny action has altered the future - he's married to a butterfly.

8.title: Episode #6.8

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

8.plot: Investigating a string of murders in which the victims were all found bound in string, a detective wonders whether the deaths are the work of 'the String Killer'. Unsure, he retires.

9.title: Episode #6.9

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

9.plot: On the anniversary of his wife's botched lobotomy, a lonely widower discovers that love has a funny way of turning up in the most unexpected places - like a toilet bowl, for example.

10.title: Episode #6.10

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

10.plot: Biopic of Arun Singh, the Calcutta dust wrangler who taught Mother Teresa to box and, for a week in July 1963, was widely regarded as the handsomest man on Earth.

11.title: Episode #6.11

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

11.plot: When a man accidentally runs over a gypsy's head, she places a terrible curse on him: for an entire year, he will urinate through his nose (after a year, it's back to the penis as normal).

12.title: Episode #6.12

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

12.plot: Trapped underground, three miners keep their spirits up by playing songs to each other on harps. In a twist ending, it turns out the miners have been dead all along and they're actually trapped underground in heaven.

1.title: Episode #7.1

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

1.plot: Seven veteran gunslingers agree to defend a poor Mexican village against an outbreak of Japanese encephalitis.

2.title: Episode #7.2

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

2.plot: An acrobat, a diplomat and a bureaucrat enter a laundromat and engage in some chit-chat about a thermostat. Stars Chow Yun-fat.

3.title: Episode #7.3

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

3.plot: In a futuristic society, all sarcasm has been eliminated except for the occasional use of the phrase "oh, do you think so?" by Nether-Zone outcasts.

4.title: Episode #7.4

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

4.plot: A priest and a tame bear travel back in time to Dallas, Texas on November 23, 1963 to try and prevent an episode of 'The Patty Duke Show' going to air.

5.title: Episode #7.5

episode of.title: Shaun Micallef's Mad as Hell (TV Series 2012–2018)

5.plot: Biopic of Entente Cordiale, the blind French plumber who, in 1886, won the contract to install the male toilets in the Statue of Liberty's head.
